Getting Started

Setting up R packages

To start with ggstatsplot and tidyverse packages will be launched using library().

packages = c('ggstatsplot','tidyverse')
for (p in packages){
  if(!require(p, character.only = T)){
    install.packages(p)
  }
}

Importing data

exam <- read_csv("data/exam_data.csv")

Working with ggstatsplot

ANOVA test - bayes

set.seed(101)
ggbetweenstats(
  data = exam,
  x = RACE, 
  y = ENGLISH,
  type = "b"
)

ANOVA test - Parametric

ggbetweenstats(
  data = exam,
  x = RACE, 
  y = ENGLISH,
  type = "p",
  mean.ci = TRUE, 
  pairwise.comparisons = TRUE, 
  pairwise.display = "s",
  p.adjust.method = "fdr",
  messages = FALSE
)
